      <memberdef kind="define" id="group__tigermodes_1ga36a6878b79537652e9810e09ac165a8f" prot="public" static="no">
        <name>NDIGO6G12_TIGER_OUTPUT</name>
        <initializer>1</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Pulse height is approximately 2&#160;V. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Connected hardware must not drive any signals to the connectors used as outputs, as doing so could damage both the Ndigo6G-12 and the external hardware. We recommend to only use short pulses to avoid undesirable baseline shift due to the AC coupling, but the device does not pose any restrictions on the duty cycle. This mode can be used as a clock output with a frequency of 75/N&#160;MHz (for integer N). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
