        <name>NDIGO6G12_TIGER_BIPOLAR</name>
        <initializer>3</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>TiGer pulses are bipolar. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Not supported for inputs TRG and GATE.</para>
<para>In this mode, the connector creates bipolar pulses with 1&#160;V amplitude. The connector can still be used as an input. Pulses have no effect on the baseline offset.</para>
<para>The TiGer should be configured with <computeroutput>start</computeroutput>= <computeroutput>stop + 1</computeroutput> for minimium-width bipolar pulses. The maximum bipolar pulse width is <ref refid="group__tigerstop_1gafdf751fd3bdecfe23abce68ef14a8d65" kindref="member">NDIGO6G12_TIGER_MAX_BIPOLAR_PULSE_LENGTH</ref>. </para>
